<br>
Yet, to this day, I still see daily outbursts in game that make me wonder about the people behind the toons.  I compare it to road rage, instances where normally rational people lose control of their emotions, and break the codes of conduct that have been culturally established to promote civil behavior between citizens.  In my book, those with a predisposition to lose control of themselves in RL, will do the same in VR, they have a weakness in character that will surface in whatever community they are a part of.  Dysfunctional people exist, and while EQ may enhance, or provide an environment with fewer repercussions for inappropriate behaviour, which further fuels their break from normalcy, I strongly feel that some people have a predisposition for addiction, and it will take root in any number of activities they engage in, and to make Sony put labels on their products will unfairly cast their product in a negative manner.  Personal Responsibility needs to be taken, and while I respect some people's needs to grieve and blame others when dealing with something as tragic as suicide, knee jerk reactions and petty lawsuits only demean the premise of free will, and the right to freely make choices in our life.  I pity the family of the deceased, I recognize how EQ provide an negative outlet for a troubled man, and how EQ can become all consuming, but others should be free to choose what entertainments they want without the taint and prejudicial connotations warning labels would illicit.<br>
